  "translations": {
    "en": "So how would they have a choice in the Imam, when the Imam is knowing and not ignorant, a tireless shepherd, the source of sanctity, purity, offering, asceticism, knowledge, and worship? He is specified by the call of the Messenger. He is of the pure, chaste lineage — there is no blemish in his ancestry, and no nobleman comes close to him. He is of the House from Quraysh, the peak of Hashim, from the progeny of the Family of the Messenger, with the approval of Allah. He is the noblest of nobles, a branch from 'Abd Manaf. He is growing in knowledge, perfect in forbearance, in charge of leadership, proficient in governance, obligatory in obedience, establishing the command of Allah, an advisor to the servants of Allah, and a protector of the religion of Allah.",
    "ur": "[حدیث امامت - حصہ 12] So how would they have a choice in the Imam, when the Imam is knowing and not ignorant, a tireless s...",
